# Performance baselines: keep the HAR (the source of truth for the
# analyzer) + the hand-curated README.md per baseline directory. Drop
# sitespeed.io's heavy binary artifacts (videos, filmstrips, key-event
# screenshots) and its prebuilt viewer bundle (HTML + CSS + JS + PNGs),
# which add tens of MB per baseline without being diff-useful.
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/pages/*/data/video/
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/pages/*/data/filmstrip/
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/pages/*/data/screenshots/
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/pages/*/*.html
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/*.html
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/css/
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/js/
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/img/
docs/perf-baselines/*/*/*.ico
